p%3EFelix%20Kunze%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EKatya%20Echazarreta%20became%20the%20first%20Mexican-born%20woman%20to%20go%20to%20space%20in%20June%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EEchazarreta%20struggled%20to%20fit%20in%20when%20her%20family%20immigrated%20to%20California%20when%20she%20was%207%20years%20old.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBut%20her%20passion%20for%20engineering%20and%20space%20propelled%20her%20forward%2C%20and%20she%20landed%20her%20dream%20job%20at%20NASA.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20essay%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Katya%20Echazarreta%2C%20a%2028-year-old%20Mexican%20electrical%20engineer%20and%20citizen%20astronaut.%20She%20became%20the%20first%20Mexican-born%20woman%20to%20go%20to%20space%20in%202022.%20The%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Guadalajara%2C%20Mexico.%20My%20childhood%20there%20was%20a%20bit%20difficult%2C%20not%20necessarily%20because%20we%20were%20in%20Mexico%2C%20but%20rather%20because%20of%20my%20sister's%20situation.%20My%20older%20sister%20has%20mental%20and%20physical%20disabilities%2C%20and%20she%20got%20meningitis%20when%20she%20was%20very%20small%2C%20leaving%20her%20with%20epilepsy%2C%20paralysis%20down%20half%20her%20body%2C%20and%20the%20mental%20state%20of%20about%20an%208-year-old%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20happened%20in%20the%20'90s%2C%20and%20the%20medical%20care%20necessary%20to%20take%20care%20of%20somebody%20like%20my%20sister%20wasn't%20available%20in%20Mexico.%20So%20my%20parents%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20immigrate%20to%20California%20when%20I%20was%207%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20transition%20was%20difficult%20for%20me%2C%20mostly%20because%20I%20didn't%20speak%20English.%20I've%20always%20been%20the%20kind%20of%20kid%20that%20found%20comfort%20and%20a%20happy%20place%20in%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20classroom%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20would%20sit%20for%20hours%20and%20hours%2C%20but%20everything%20was%20nonsense%20to%20me%20because%20I%20didn't%20understand%20English.%20I%20started%20to%20fall%20behind%2C%20and%20was%20also%20made%20fun%20of.%20Knowing%20you're%20bullied%20but%20not%20knowing%20what%20it's%20about%20because%20you%20don't%20understand%20what%20they're%20saying%20%E2%80%94%20it%20just%20feeds%20into%20it%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELearning%20English%20became%20my%20number-one%20priority.%20If%20I%20was%20going%20to%20learn%20about%20space%20and%20science%20%E2%80%94%20which%20I'd%20always%20been%20curious%20and%20passionate%20about%20%E2%80%94%20I%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20master%20the%20language.%20Everything%20in%20my%20life%20needed%20to%20be%20in%20English%2C%20from%20the%20books%20and%20articles%20I%20read%2C%20to%20the%20TV%20shows%20and%20movies%20I%20watched.%20I%20only%20spoke%20Spanish%20to%20my%20mom%2C%20who%20still%20hadn't%20learned%20English%20at%20that%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20how%20to%20communicate%20basic%20language%20by%20the%20time%20I%20was%20in%20the%20fourth%20grade%2C%20which%20was%20a%20year%20later.%20By%20the%20fifth%20grade%2C%20I%20was%20already%20reading%2C%20writing%2C%20and%20speaking%20at%20a%20fifth-grader's%20level.%20And%20then%2C%20by%20the%20time%20I%20made%20it%20to%20the%20sixth%20grade%2C%20I%20was%20reading%2C%20writing%2C%20and%20speaking%20at%20an%20eighth-grade%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Katya%20Echazarreta%20as%20a%20child%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652836236561dd877e793fd8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22809%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEchazarreta%20was%20interested%20in%20space%20and%20engineering%20from%20a%20young%20age.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Katya%20Echazarreta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EFrom%20handmade%20space%20journals%20to%20NASA%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20binder%20in%20early%20elementary%20school%2C%20where%20I%20had%20a%20section%20for%20the%20different%20planets%20in%20our%20solar%20system.%20We%20hooked%20up%20my%20first%20computer%20I'd%20gotten%20for%20Christmas%20to%20the%20family%20printer%2C%20and%2C%20anytime%20I%20learned%20anything%20new%20about%20the%20planets%2C%20I'd%20print%20it%20out%20and%20add%20it%20to%20my%20binder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20had%20a%20section%20on%20Mars%2C%20and%20if%20I%20learned%20anything%20new%20about%20its%20composition%2C%20temperature%2C%20or%20how%20long%20its%20days%20are%2C%20I'd%20add%20those%20little%20bits%20of%20information%2C%20so%20I%20had%20my%20own%20little%20scientific%20journal%20of%20everything%20I%20was%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20my%20interest%20and%20education%20in%20space%20became%20more%20formalized.%20I%20signed%20myself%20up%20for%20online%20astronomy%20classes%20when%20I%20was%20in%20elementary%20school%20using%20my%20mom's%20name.%20I%20did%20my%20homework%20and%20took%20the%20tests%20%E2%80%94%20nobody%20probably%20knew%20it%20was%20a%2012-year-old%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Katya%20Echazarreta%20in%20an%20aircraft%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6528365268f1d46f52b0553c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22809%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20young%20Echazarreta%20in%20a%20simulator%20aircraft.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Katya%20Echazarreta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20UCLA%20for%20college%20and%20majored%20in%20electrical%20engineering%2C%20and%20I%20landed%20my%20dream%20job%20at%20NASA's%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20as%20an%20intern%20before%20I%20was%20hired%20full%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20at%20NASA%20was%20surreal.%20The%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Lab%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20all%20the%20robotics-led%20missions%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasas-curiosity-rover-discover-mars-climate-history-2021-4%5C%22%3ECuriosity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjupiter-moon-europa-ocean-water-plume-evidence-2018-5%5C%22%3EGalileo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjuno-vs-galileo-nasa-missions-jupiter-2016-8%5C%22%3EJuno%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20these%20missions%20that%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-voyager-pictures-45-year-journey-neptune-uranus-saturn-earth-2022-6%5C%22%3Etaught%20us%20so%20much%20about%20our%20solar%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20these%20moments%20where%20I%20snap%20back%20into%20the%20reality%20of%20my%20job%20and%20realize%20that%20my%20normal%20workday%20and%20paperwork%20is%20what's%20helping%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmars-rover-wiggles-its-wheels-as-it-prepares-for-first-test-drive-2012-8%5C%22%3EMars%20Rover%20take%20its%20first%20test%20drive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAngling%20for%20space%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20I%20heard%20about%20Space%20for%20Humanity%2C%20a%20non-profit%20program%20that%20sent%20citizen%20astronauts%20into%20space.%20I%20applied%20almost%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20hear%20back%20until%20three%20years%20later%2C%20but%20during%20that%20time%2C%20I%20completed%20a%20space%20training%20program%20where%20I%20did%20training%20with%20microgravity%2C%20G-force%2C%20and%20pressurized%20spacesuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20heard%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspaceforhumanity.org%2Fblog%2Fca-1announcement%3Flocale%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20was%20selected%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20of%207%2C000%20applicants%20from%20over%20120%20countries%2C%20I%20had%20to%20jump%20on%20psychological%20training%2C%20because%20my%20mission%20was%20to%20analyze%20the%20effects%20on%20a%20human%20being%20when%20you're%20able%20to%20look%20at%20the%20planet%20fr