ed%20country%20could%20offer%20a%20wealth%20of%20coveted%20mineral%20resources.%20A%20mines%20minister%20estimated%20in%202010%20that%20Afghanistan%20had%20untapped%20deposits%2C%20ranging%20from%20copper%20to%20gold%20and%20lithium%2C%20worth%20between%20%241%20trillion%20and%20%243%20trillion.%20It%20is%20not%20clear%20how%20much%20they%20are%20worth%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20been%20in%20talks%20with%20the%20Taliban%20over%20plans%2C%20begun%20under%20the%20previous%20foreign-backed%20government%2C%20over%20a%20possible%20huge%20copper%20mine%20in%20eastern%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina's%20foreign%20ministry%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAzizi%20will%20continue%20discussions%20in%20Beijing%20on%20plans%20to%20build%20a%20road%20through%20the%20Wakhan%20corridor%2C%20a%20thin%2C%20mountainous%20strip%20in%20northern%20Afghanistan%2C%20to%20provide%20direct%20access%20to%20China%2C%20Akhundzada%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOfficials%20from%20China%2C%20the%20Taliban%2C%20and%20neighbouring%20Pakistan%20said%20in%20May%20they%20would%20like%20Belt%20and%20Road%20to%20include%20Afghanistan%20and%20for%20the%20flagship%20China-Pakistan%20Economic%20Corridor%20to%20be%20extended%20across%20the%20border%20to%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Taliban%20has%20not%20been%20formally%20recognised%20by%20any%20government%20since%20taking%20control%20of%20Afghanistan%20two%20years%20ago%20as%20U.S.%20and%20other%20foreign%20forces%20withdrew.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20series%20of%20restrictions%20on%20women's%20access%20to%20public%20life%20and%20the%20barring%20of%20many%20female%20NGO%20staff%20from%20work%20has%20increased%20roadblocks%20to%20recognition%2C%20especially%20by%20Western%20countries%2C%20officials%20and%20international%20relations%20analysts%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20boosted%20engagement%20with%20the%20Taliban%2C%20becoming%20the%20first%20country%20to%20appoi