3EThis%20year%2C%20my%20%24200%2C000%20student%20debt%20was%20forgiven.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI'm%20now%20able%20to%20think%20about%20my%20future%20and%20buy%20a%20house%20for%20my%20family.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Linda%20Whitman.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%201987%20when%20I%20started%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loan-repayments-cant-buy-home-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20journey%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Adams%20State%20College%20%E2%80%94%20now%20Adams%20State%20University%20%E2%80%94%20in%20Alamosa%2C%20Colorado.%20I%20was%2017%20and%20dreamed%20of%20becoming%20a%20high-school%20counselor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaking-a-semester-off-college-student-yale-burnout-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esemester%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%20life%20events%20prevented%20me%20from%20studying%20full%20time%20until%201992.%20I%20graduated%20in%20May%201995%20with%20my%20bachelor's%20in%20psychology%20and%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-recent-college-grads-get-work-ready-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egraduate%3C%2Fa%3E%20work%20in%20counseling.%20Life%20circumstances%20struck%20again%2C%20and%20I'm%20still%20five%20classes%20short%20of%20getting%20that%20graduate%20degree.%20I%20eventually%20changed%20direction%20and%20went%20into%20construction%20management%20%E2%80%94%20the%20field%20I've%20worked%20in%20for%20nearly%2022%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstudentaid.gov%2Fmanage-loans%2Frepayment%2Fplans%2Fincome-driven%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eincome-driven%20repayment%20plan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20was%20created%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnche.ed.gov%2Flegislation%2Fcollege-cost-reduction-and-access%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520College%2520Cost%2520Reduction%2520and%2Cpurposes%2520of%2520federal%2520financial%2520aid.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECollege%20Cost%20Reduction%20and%20Access%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202007%20to%20make%20education%20more%20affordable%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstudentaid.gov%2Fannouncements-events%2Fidr-account-adjustment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone-time%20adjustment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20resulted%20in%20my%20full%20loan%20forgiveness%20in%20August%20at%20age%2053.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHardships%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20make%20student-loan%20payments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20a%20bad%20car%20accident%20in%20fall%201996%2C%20which%20gave%20me%20brain%20trauma.%20I%20tried%20one%20more%20semester%20of%20school%2C%20but%20I%20had%20to%20leave%20the%20counseling%20program.%20What%20I%20borrowed%20between%20my%20undergraduate%20and%20graduate%20work%20was%20about%20%2460%2C000%2C%20and%20it%20ballooned%20to%20more%20than%20%24200%2C000%20because%20of%20the%20compound%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20now-ex-husband%20went%20to%20prison%2C%20I%20became%20a%20single%20mom%20to%20five%20kids.%20I%20moved%20to%20Washington%20%E2%80%94%20to%20an%20island%20that%20doesn't%20have%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20high-paying%20jobs.%20The%20first%20opportunity%20I%20got%20was%20working%20in%20a%20kitchen%2C%20and%20I%20then%20got%20an%20offer%20to%20go%20into%20construction%20and%20work%20at%20the%20office%20front%20desk.%20I%20did%20everything%20I%20could.%20I%20was%20working%2040%20hours%20a%20week%20at%20%2413%20an%20hour%2C%20which%20eventually%20increased%20to%20%2416.50%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20awful.%20I%20wanted%20to%20pay%20my%20student%20loans%2C%20but%20it%20was%20more%20important%20to%20provide%20for%20my%20family.%20Even%20with%20state%20assistance%20%E2%80%94%20including%20food%20stamps%20and%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20there%20wasn't%20enough%20money.%20I%20reconsolidated%20my%20loans%20twice%20so%20I%20could%20continue%20deferring%20them.%20I%20couldn't%20deal%20with%20it%2C%20so%20I%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20student%20loans%20were%20finally%20forgiven%20under%20the%20Biden%20administration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20I%20received%20an%20email%20from%20the%20Education%20Department%20saying%20I%20was%20eligible%20to%20have%20my%20loans%20forgiven.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20granted%20a%20one-time%20adjustment%20for%20everyone%20who%20owed%20student%20debt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ed.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fbiden-harris-administration-begins-discharges-804000-borrowers-39-billion-automatic-loan-forgiveness-result-fixes-income-driven-repayment-plans%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBorrowers%2520are%2520eligible%2520for%2520forgiveness%2Cdischarged%2520over%2520the%2520coming%2520weeks.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efor%2020%20to%2025%20years%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20forgiveness%20wasn't%20sudden.%20My%20debt%20on%20August%201%20was%20%24201%2C324.52.%20Now%2C%20granted%2C%20I%20didn't%20borrow%20that%20much%3B%20that%20number%20is%20thanks%20to%20interest.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2014%2C%20I%20looked%20again%20and%20found%20that%20over%20%2488%2C000%20had%20been%20forgiven.%20It%20was%20the%20undergraduate%20portion.%20I%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20thank%20you%2C%20Lord.%26quot%3B%20That%20was%20awesome.%20It%20cut%20my%20loans%20almost%20in%20half.%20This%20was%20a%20huge%20blessing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20August%2C%20I%20figured%20I%20needed%20to%20find%20out%20what%20my%20new%20payment%20would%20be%20come%20October.%20I%20looked%2C%20and%20it%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPaid%20in%20full.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20balance%20was%20zero.%20I%20just%20screamed%20in%20shock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20life%20has%20changed%20after%20student-loan%20forgiveness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20posted%20on%20Facebook%20to%20thank%20every%20taxpayer%20for%20contributing%20to%20my%20loan%20forgiveness%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20comments%20from%20my%20%26quot%3Bfriends%26quot%3B%20were%20saddening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTell%20me%20how%20that%20is%20fair.%20No%20one%20is%20helping%20me%20pay%20off%20my%20mortgage%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20commented.%20Another%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BHere's%20a%20thought%E2%80%A6Pay%20your%20loans%20back%20yourself.%20Be%20responsible%20for%20yourself!%20If%20you%20can't%20afford%20to%20pay%20back%20a%20loan%20don't%20borrow%20the%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20sit%20in%20my%20excitement%20now%20with%20just%20a%20few%20close%20family%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20been%20trying%20for%20the%20past%20seven%20or%20eight%20years%20to%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20but%20my%20loans%20were%20stopping%20me.%20Now%20I%20will%20finally%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that%2C%20and%20I'm%20so%20excited.%20I%20had%20been%20feeling%20like%20I'd%20failed%20to%20achieve%20the%20American%20dream%20of%20owning%20a%20home.%20However%2C%20when%20I%20saw%20my%20student-loan%20statement%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BPaid%20in%20full%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20knew%20this%20dream%20would%20finally%20be%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20just%20grateful%3B%20I'm%20just%20so%20thankful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mother-in-student-loan-debt-loans-forgiven-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697279881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6528179268f1d46f52b02301%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mother-in-student-loan-debt-loans-forgiven-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22She%20couldn't%20afford%20her%20student-loan%20payments%20because%20she%20was%20raising%20five%20kids%20on%20her%20own.%20But%20her%20loans%20were%20forgiven%20this%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kristina%20Puga)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mother-in-student-loan-debt-loans-forgiven-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Warren%20Buffett's%20deputy%20spoke%20about%20his%20'tiger%20mom%2C'%20taking%20risks%2C%20and%20having%20a%20short%20seller's%20eye.%20Here%20are%20Todd%20Combs'%208%20best%20quotes%20from%20a%20new%20interview.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221545%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Todd%20Combs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652570ee55f52b01b35b0e41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22772%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETodd%20Combs%2C%20one%20of%20Warren%20Buffett's%20two%20investment%20managers%20at%20Berkshire%20Hathaway.%3Cp%3EYahoo%20Finance%2FYouTube%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ETodd%20Combs%20discussed%20his%20demanding%20mother%2C%20passion%20for%20investing%2C%20and%20willingness%20to%20take%20risks.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EHe%20compared%20studying%20a%20business%20to%20being%20a%20detective%2C%20and%20touted%20his%20short%20seller's%20eye.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ECombs%20is%20one%20of%20Warren%20Buffett's%20two%20investment%20managers%20at%20Berkshire%20Hathaway.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETodd%20Combs%20spoke%20about%20his%20mother's%20sky-high%20expectations%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20taking%20risks%2C%20and%20the%20need%20for%20intense%20passion%20and%20ambition%20to%20achieve%20excellence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombs%20helps%20Warren%20Buffett%20manage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fbrk-b-stock%5C%22%3EBerkshire%20Hathaway%3C%2Fa%3E's%20vast%20portfolio%20of%20stocks%20and%20other%20investments%2C%20and%20serves%20as%20CEO%20of%20Berkshire-owned%20Geico.%20He%20compared%20digging%20into%20a%20company%20to%20detective%20work%2C%20and%20underlined%20the%20value%20of%20having%20a%20short%20seller's%20eye%20when%20analyzing%20businesses.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-charlie-munger-todd-combs-stocks-portfolio-manager-berkshire-2023-10%5C%22%3Emade%20the%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.joincolossus.com%2Fepisodes%2F14034172%2Fcombs-todd-combs-investing-the-last-liberal-art%3Ftab%3Dtranscript%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20episode%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BArt%20of%20Investing%26quot%3B%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHere%20are%20Combs'%208%20best%20quotes%2C%20lightly%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20%26quot%3BMy%20mother%20could%20have%20been%20a%20CEO%20in%20her%20own%20right.%20She%20didn't%20go%20to%20college%20because%20she%20didn't%20have%20an%20opportunity%20back%20then.%20So%20I%20think%20she%20wanted%20to%20channel%20all%20those%20missed%20opportunities%20in%20her%20life%20into%20mine.%20I'll%20never%20forget%20coming%20home%20one%20time%20with%20an%20A-%2C%20and%20I%20think%20I%20got%20grounded%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20stuff.%20So%20she%20was%20very%2C%20very%20militant.%20She%20was%20the%20original%20tiger%20mom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20super%2C%20super%20important%20to%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20risk%20when%20you're%20young.%20You've%20got%20nothing%20to%20lose%20at%20your%20age%2C%20you%20take%20the%20risk%20and%20you%20can%20massively%20screw%20up%2C%20and%20nobody's%20going%20to%20really%20hold%20it%20against%20you%20unless%20it's%20fraud%20or%20something%20like%20that.%20Take%20intelligent%20risk%2C%20don't%20take%20stupid%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20do%20with%20a%20jigsaw%20puzzle%3F%20You%20dump%20out%20all%20the%20pieces%20and%20you%20start%20with%20the%20edges%20and%20the%20corners.%20You%20don't%20start%20in%20the%20middle%20and%20build%20your%20way%20out.%26quot%3B%20(Exploring%20different%20fields%20and%20taking%20risks%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20make%20your%20mistakes%20early%20and%20find%20your%20passion%2C%20Combs%20said.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20usually%20rise%20to%20their%20level%20of%20complacency.%20If%20your%20dream%20is%20to%20make%20it%20to%20manager%20and%20you're%20perfectly%20fine%20there%2C%20that's%20pretty%20much%20where%20you're%20going%20to%20stop.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20if%20you've%20got%2010%2C000%20people%20who%20all%20want%20to%20be%20CEO%20or%20whatever%20that%20they're%20all%20going%20to%20achieve%20it%2C%20but%20people%20create%20their%20own%20limiting%20factors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20never%20really%20been%20ready%20for%20anything%20in%20my%20life.%20When%20people%20see%20things%20in%20you%20that%20you%20don't%20see%20in%20yourself%2C%20that's%20amazing.%20And%20that%20was%20true%20with%20Steve.%20That%20was%20certainly%20true%20with%20Charlie.%20That%20was%20true%20with%20Warren%2C%20multiple%20times%20with%20Warren%20for%20Berkshire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20like%20the%20detective%20that%20could%20show%20them%20the%20map%20and%20the%20terrain%20and%20tear%20it%20all%20apart.%20I'm%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20yes%2C%20this%20is%20a%20total%20fraud%2C'%20and%20I'm%20triangulating%20all%20this%20stuff%2C%20putting%20the%20puzzle%20pieces%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.%20%26quot%3BShort%20selling%20is%20no%20different%20than%20long%20investing%20in%20my%20humble%20opinion.%20Very%2C%20very%2C%20very%20few%20people%20know%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%20it's%20very%20hard.%20You%20don't%20have%20a%20primary%20care%20physician%20go%20do%20brain%20surgery.%20I%20always%20felt%20you%20had%20to%20be%20about%2080%25%2C%2085%25%20correct%20on%20the%20short%20side%20to%20make%20money.%20