0for%20those%20who%20want%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20like%20mine.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222420%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tr%C3%A9%20Moment%20standing%20on%20a%20balcony.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65282fea6561dd877e793417%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221816%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETr%C3%A9%20Moment%20has%20been%20a%20nanny%20for%20high-profile%20and%20high-net-worth%20families%20for%20eight%20years.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Tr%C3%A9%20Moment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETr%C3%A9%20Moment%20works%20as%20a%20nanny%20for%20high-profile%20and%20high-net-worth%20families.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoment%20says%20it's%20essential%20to%20set%20boundaries%20when%20working%20with%20affluent%20families.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20says%20her%20career%20is%20very%20rewarding%2C%20but%20you%20shouldn't%20do%20it%20to%20get%20rich%20quickly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Tr%C3%A9%20Moment%2C%20a%20childcare%20professional%20and%20business%20owner%20who%20has%20worked%20with%20high-profile%20and%20high-net-worth%20families%20since%202015.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20career%20as%20a%20nanny%20for%20high-net-worth%20families%20is%20just%20as%20fun%20as%20it%20is%20unpredictable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20nannying%20in%202015%20for%20elite%20clients%20and%20have%20since%20started%20my%20own%20childcare%20and%20home%20care%20business.%20While%20I'm%20based%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20Georgia%2C%20I've%20worked%20in%20several%20major%20metropolitan%20areas%2C%20and%20I%20manage%20employees%20in%20Mexico%2C%20Jamaica%2C%20and%20Western%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20tips%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20known%20before%20taking%20on%20this%20rewarding%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBe%20prepared%20for%20last-minute%20travel%20with%20high-security%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20high-profile%20clients%2C%20security%20measures%20are%20usually%20very%20strict.%20You%20deal%20with%20checking%20in%20with%20security%2C%20making%20sure%20no%20one%20knows%20who%20you%20are%20working%20with.%20That%20often%20means%20you%20can't%20tell%20anyone%20where%20you%20are%20when%20you're%20with%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20also%20have%20to%20be%20prepared%20for%20anything%20with%20high-profile%20or%20high-net-worth%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20experience%20is%20invaluable%20for%20your%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20they%20often%20travel%20on%20very%20short%20notice.%20Sometimes%2C%20you%20may%20not%20know%20until%2010%20minutes%20before%20that%20you're%20heading%20out%20of%20the%20country.%20You%20just%20have%20to%20have%20your%20passport%20ready%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20possible%20to%20work%20for%20elite%20clients%20who%20fly%20under%20the%20radar%20because%20they're%20not%20public-facing.%20Working%20for%20those%20families%20tends%20to%20be%20more%20relaxed%2C%20and%20travel%20plans%20tend%20to%20be%20made%20further%20ahead%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221815%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tr%C3%A9%20Moment%20taking%20a%20selfie%20while%20looking%20out%20the%20window%20on%20an%20airplane.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65294d0d55f52b01b35ed5c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221361%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMoment%20told%20Insider%20that%20people%20looking%20to%20nanny%20for%20high-profile%20families%20should%20be%20prepared%20for%20last-minute%20travel.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Tr%C3%A9%20Moment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20sure%20to%20set%20your%20own%20boundaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20not%20get%20overwhelmed%20in%20this%20work%20environment%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20protect%20yourself%20as%20an%20employee%20%E2%80%94%20is%20always%20to%20set%20clear%20boundaries%20and%20advocate%20for%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20high-profile%20and%20high-net-worth%20individuals%20have%20people%20advocating%20for%20them%2C%20their%20family%2C%20and%20their%20household.%20So%2C%20if%20you%20are%20not%20able%20to%20advocate%20for%20yourself%2C%20then%20you%20will%20end%20up%20getting%20the%20short%20end%20of%20the%20stick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20some%20of%20my%20boundaries%20have%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20payment%20and%20timeliness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20in%20my%20contracts%20a%20clause%20for%20immediate%20termination%2C%20and%20some%20of%20that%20has%20to%20do%20with%20being%20late%20on%20payments.%20A%20lot%20of%20families%20are%20not%20always%20actively%20looking%20at%20their%20checklist%2C%20and%20the%20payroll%20messes%20up%20sometimes%2C%20or%20they%20just%20don't%20pay%20you%20on%20time.%20Then%20you%20leave%20the%20house%20and%20you%20still%20haven't%20been%20paid%2C%20which%20to%20me%20is%20inappropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELateness%20is%20also%20a%20key%20issue%20to%20keep%20in%20mind.%20For%20the%20employer%2C%20they're%20just%20coming%20home%20from%20work%2C%20so%20being%20late%20might%20not%20be%20on%20their%20mind%20or%20seem%20like%20a%20problem.%20They%20don't%20think%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20as%20a%20caregiver%2C%20as%20a%20care%20provider%2C%20I%20want%20to%20go%20home.%20And%20so%20sometimes%20they're%20late%205%2C%2010%2C%2015%20minutes%20here%20and%20there.%20But%20over%20time%2C%20those%2015%20minutes%20add%20up%20and%20it's%20taking%20me%20longer%20and%20longer%20to%20get%20home%2C%20and%20now%20my%20family%20is%20without%20me%20even%20longer%2C%20or%20I'm%20not%20getting%20paid%20for%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20boundary%20might%20be%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20cannot%20be%20late.%26quot%3B%20Or%2C%20it%20could%20be%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20late%2C%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20late%20fee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20are%20the%20only%20person%20that%20can%20advocate%20for%20you%2C%20and%20your%20contract%20is%20the%20one%20place%20where%20you%20get%20to%20take%20care%20of%20all%20of%20your%20needs%20so%20that%20you%20don't%20end%20up%20burned%20out%2C%20upset%2C%20pissed%20off%2C%20or%20working%20for%20a%20family%20that%20does%20not%20actually%20give%20you%20what%20you%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20get%20into%20it%20for%20the%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20a%20get-rich-quick%20career.%20Employers%20need%20to%20respect%20the%20role%20and%20pay%20fairly%2C%20but%20you%20also%20shouldn't%20get%20into%20this%20unless%20you're%20passionate%20about%20caregiving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20field%20should%20be%20looked%20down%20upon.%20Some%20families%20think%20people%20just%20want%20to%20make%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20money%20doing%20this%20career%2C%20and%20they%20say%20to%20themselves%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20but%20they're%20just%20a%20nanny.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20some%20new%20nannies%20think%20to%20themselves%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20good%20with%20my%20little%20brother%20and%20sister%2C%20so%20I%20can%20do%20this%20to%20make%20money%20or%20get%20myself%20through%20school.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20true.%20Every%20single%20family%20and%20every%20single%20child%20is%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20only%20in%20it%20to%20make%20money%20and%20not%20because%20you%20actually%20enjoy%20helping%20people%20because%20this%20is%20a%20care%20field%2C%20then%20your%20best%20bet%20is%20to%20do%20something%20that%20does%20not%20require%20you%20to%20actively%20be%20present%20in%20other%20people's%20lives%20where%20they%20have%20to%20depend%20on%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-nanny-of-wealthy-high-profile-family-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%