k%20towards%20turning%20Mok-ha's%20dream%20into%20reality.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Fextraordinary-attorney-woo-actress-park-eun-bin-all-set-to-charm-fans-as-a-songstress-in-castaway-diva%2Farticleshow%2F104420986.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Guinness%20Book's%202024%20Edition%20Gets%20Over%2060%20Records%20From%20India.%20Details%20Here%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20edition%20of%20the%20Guinness%20World%20Records%20has%202%2C638%20achievements%20from%20around%20the%20world%2C%20including%20over%2060%20from%20India%20with%20the%20entry%20on%20rainfall%20in%20Meghalaya's%20Cherrapunji%20being%20one%20of%20the%20oldest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDistributed%20in%20India%20by%20Penguin%20Random%20House%2C%20the%20book%20has%20nine%20fact-packed%20chapters%20-%20Blue%20Planet%2C%20Aquatic%20Life%2C%20Humans%2C%20Recordology%2C%20Adventures%2C%20History%2C%20Science%20and%20Technology%2C%20Arts%20and%20Media%2C%20and%20Sports%20-%20and%20five%20special%20features%3A%20Hall%20of%20Fame%2C%20Young%20Achievers%2C%20Gaming%2C%20Explainers%2C%20and%20Bucket%20List.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20edition%20is%20the%20final%20installment%20in%20the%20partnership%20with%20award-winning%20artist%20Rod%20Hunt.%20According%20to%20the%20publishers%2C%20completing%20the%20illustrated%20Guinness%20World%20Records%20universe%2C%20the%20cover%20artwork%20takes%20readers%20on%20a%20deep-sea%20odyssey%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20oldest%20records%20involving%20India%20is%20related%20to%20rainfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2015-16%2C%201995%2C%20Cherrapunji%2C%20a%20high-altitude%20town%20in%20Meghalaya%2C%20received%202.493%20m%20(8%20ft%202%20in)%20of%20rain%20over%20the%20complete%2048-hour%20period%2C%20the%20record%20book%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20this%20normally%20means%20that%20the%20region%20gets%20a%20high%20level%20of%20annual%20rainfall%2C%20this%20is%20the%20most%20extreme%2048-hour%20period%20on%20record%20-%20as%20verified%20by%20the%20World%20Meteorological%20Organisation%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20calendar%20month%2C%20the%20record%20is%209%2C300%20mm%20(366%20in)%20at%20Cherrapunji%20in%20July%201861%20and%20the%2012-month%20record%20was%20also%20set%20at%20Cherrapunji%2C%20with%2026%2C461%20mm%20(1%2C041.75%20in)%20between%20August%201%2C%201860%20and%20July%2031%2C%201861%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20adds.%20Between%20August%201%2C%201860%20and%20July%2031%2C%201861%2C%20a%20total%20of%2026%2C470%20mm%20(1%2C042%20in)%20of%20rain%20fell%20at%20Cherrapunji%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Meteorological%20Organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20record%20which%20holds%20good%20since%201937.%20It%20is%20Jalakanyaka%20(or%20Mermaid)%20by%20Indian%20sculptor%20Kanayi%20Kunhiraman%2C%20the%20largest%20sculpture%20of%20a%20merperson%20in%20the%20world.%20Reclining%20in%20a%20shell-shaped%20pool%20at%20Shankumugham%20Beach%20in%20Thiruvananthapuram%20in%20Kerala%2C%20the%20concrete%20mermaid%20is%2026.5%20m%20(87%20ft)%20long%20and%207.6%20m%20(25%20ft)%20tall.%20The%20shell%20within%20which%20she%20lies%20is%20approximately%2032%20m%20(105%20ft)%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20record%20for%20the%20first%20and%20fastest%20man%20and%20woman%20to%20have%20circumnavigated%20the%20earth%20by%20car%2C%20covering%20six%20continents%20under%20the%20rules%20applicable%20in%201989%20and%201991%20embracing%20more%20than%20an%20equator's%20length%20of%20driving%20(24%2C901%20road%20miles%3B%2040%2C075km)%2C%20is%20held%20by%20Saloo%20Choudhury%20and%20his%20wife%20Neena%20Choudhury.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20journey%20took%2069%20days%2019%20hours%205%20minutes%20from%20September%209%20to%20November%2017%2C%201989.%20The%20couple%20drove%20a%201989%20Hindustan%20%26quot%3BContessa%20Classic%26quot%3B%20starting%20and%20finishing%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndian%20folk%20musician%20Thanga%20Darlong%20(b.%2020%20July%201920)%20was%2098%20years%20319%20days%20old%20when%20he%20was%20presented%20with%20the%20Padma%20Shri%20civilian%20award%20on%20June%204%2C%202019.%20Born%20at%20Muruai%20village%20in%20Tripura%2C%20Darlong%20is%20celebrated%20as%20the%20last%20tribal%20musician%20to%20play%20the%20'rosem'%2C%20a%20flute-like%20instrument%20made%20from%20wood%2C%20bamboo%20and%20a%20traditional%20water%20pot%20used%20by%20the%20state's%20Darlong%20tribe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20shortest%20woman%20living%20is%20Nagpur's%20Jyoti%20Amge%20(born%20Dec%2016%2C%201993)%2C%20who%20measured%2062.8%20cm%20(24.7%20in).%20The%20largest%20gathering%20of%20people%20born%20prematurely%20is%20445%20and%20was%20achieved%20by%20Rainbow%20Hospitals%20India%2C%20Indian%20Foundation%20for%20Premature%20Babies%20and%20Abbott%20Healthcare%20Pvt.Ltd%20(all%20India)%20at%20the%20Park%20Hyatt%20in%20Hyderabad%20on%20November%2017%2C%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20longest-running%20sitcom%20on%20TV%20(by%20episode%20count)%20is%20%26quot%3BTaarak%20Mehta%20Ka%20Ooltah%20Chashmah%26quot%3B%20(SAB%20TV)%2C%20which%20has%20aired%203500%20episodes%2C%20as%20of%20July%202%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20largest%2C%20tallest%20and%20most%20expensive%20private%20house%20in%20the%20world%20is%20businessman%20Mukesh%20Ambani's%2027-storey%20personal%20skyscraper%20Antilia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%201%2C154%20sites%20recognised%20by%20UNESCO%2C%20the%20Taj%20Mahal%20in%20Agra%2C%20is%20currently%20the%20most%20searched-for%20World%20Heritage%20Site%20racking%20up%201.4%20million%20searches%20in%20the%20month%20of%20March%202022%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20published%20by%20Zitango%20Travel%20in%20April%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20record%20holders%20include%20Tamil%20Nadu's%20J%20Jessica%20(most%20rotations%20of%20213%20of%20a%20hula%20hoop%20on%20one%20foot%20whilst%20in%20headstand%20position%20in%20one%20minute)%20and%20Rooba%20Ganesan%20(longest%20time%20of%201%20hr%2015%20min%205%20sec%20to%20hold%20the%20mermaid%20yoga%20pose)%3B%20Aditya%20Pacholi%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20(largest%20turban%20of%20345.25%20m%C2%B2)%3B%20and%20Guinness%20Rishi%20(most%20flags%20tattooed%20on%20the%20body%20at%20366).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20edition's%20editor%20in%20chief%20Craig%20Glenday%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20GWR%202024%20edition%20is%20the%20end%20product%20of%20a%20year%20in%20which%20nearly%2030%2C000%20applications%20were%20reviewed%20by%20our%20records%20managers.%20Only%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20claims%20have%20made%20it%20through%20the%20selection%20process%2C%20so%20the%202%2C638%20records%20featured%20in%20the%20book%20really%20are%20the%20cream%20of%20this%20year's%20crop.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20inspired%20by%20our%20Blue%20Planet%20to%20celebrate%20a%20number%20of%20underwater%20records%20-%20including%20those%20set%20by%20the%20most%20impressive%20marine%20creatures%2C%20the%20most%20adventurous%20sailors%2C%20and%20even%20the%20most%20acrobatic%20mermaids!%20-%20but%2C%20as%20ever%2C%20we've%20covered%20the%20widest%20possible%20spectrum%20of%20record-breaking%2C%20from%20the%20hairiest%20humans%20to%20the%20most%20talented%20guinea%20pigs%2C%20the%20most%20dastardly%20pirates%20to%20the%20fastest%20rollercoasters%2C%20and%20the%20best-selling%20manga%20to%20the%20most%20celebrated%20athletes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3Cbr%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697273880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fb06mbruo_guinness-book-2024_625x300_14_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fww